## Architecture Decisions Already Made

1. Shared-schema-with-RLS for multi-tenancy (not schema-per-tenant)
2. Static TypeScript files for questions (not database-stored)
3. Supabase RLS pen-test script required in CI before pilot
4. Scoring engine: copy algorithm, extend for partial inputs — no refactor
5. Nullable FK pattern for remediation actions (not polymorphic)
6. Consulting firm brand on all output (AlphaPi invisible to clients)
7. Dimension-selective UX: partial completion is a first-class workflow
8. Attorney review is a hard gate before first pilot (not before build)

8 decisions deferred to architecture spike session:
- Supabase auth strategy (email/password vs magic link vs SSO)
- Session token handling + rotation policy
- File storage strategy for exported PDFs
- Background job approach for score calculation at scale
- API rate limiting strategy
- Staging environment topology
- Error monitoring and observability stack
- Feature flag strategy

